{
  "text": "The discovered model correctly partitions the attributes into synonym attributes. The only error is that the model, while mapping ln to au in C 1 , does not further group fn with ln for a complex matching to au -because the model was only designed to handle 1:1 matchings. In fact, the complete results (not shown here, see [CITATION_1] ) includes a second model, in which fn (but not ln) corresponds to au. Our study clearly indicates that, without any semantic annotations of the vocabulary, it is possible to achieve remarkable accuracy with a statistical framework. Please refer to [CITATION_2] for more technical details and experimental evaluations.",
